OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Tue 2 Jun to Thu 11 Jun
OL,6,FDuring the first week of June,
OL,7,FAtlantic weather systems are expected
OL,8,Fto move in from the west, bringing
OL,9,Fshowers or longer spells of rain at
OL,10,Ftimes. The best of the drier
OL,11,Fconditions are more likely towards the
OL,12,Fsouth and east, with more frequent
OL,13,Frain across the west and northwest,
OL,14,Falthough there will be drier
OL,15,Finterludes here also. Drier weather
OL,16,Fmay start to become more dominant as
OL,17,Fwe head into the second week of June.
OL,18,FTemperatures will be near-normal
OL,19,Foverall, with the warmest spots most
OL,20,Flikely across eastern areas. It will
OL,21,Falso be breezy at times, especially
OL,22,Facross western parts, and notably so
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Faround exposed coasts.
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
PN,16303
